title: Stella Dallas - 1937 - Barbara Stanwyck - Multisubs
description:
Produced by Sam Goldwyn, this second film version
of Olive Higgins Prouty's Stella Dallas is by far
the best. The combined talents of Goldwyn,
director King Vidor and star Barbara Stanwyck lift
this property far above the level of mere soap opera.
Stanwyck is perfectly cast as Stella Martin,
the loud, vulgar factory-town girl who snares
wealthy husband Stephen Dallas.
When Stephen is offered a job in New York,
Stella stays behind, knowing that she'll never be
part of her husband's social circle. 

Director: King Vidor
Stars: Barbara Stanwyck, John Boles, Anne Shirley
